"https://github.com/example/repo/tree/main/tests/src/org.example/library/$version$\",\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:155:To populate `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `description` fields in matching `index.json` entries:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:207:For metadata located at `metadata/<group_id>/<artifact_id>/<version>`, the corresponding test code is expected to be at `tests/src/<group_id>/<artifact_id>/<version>`.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:208:This path can be overridden to allow multiple metadata versions to share the same set of test code. This mapping is handled by the local metadata index file (`metadata/<group_id>/<artifact_id>/index.json`).\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:209:If an entry in this index contains the optional `test-version` field, the test code is resolved to the path: `tests/src/<group_id>/<artifact_id>/<test-version>`.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:222:This file must be placed under `/tests/src/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<versionId>`.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:274:   * community-tested (the library is partially tested through some project, e.g. [Reachability Metadata Repository](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/master/tests/src))\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/Utils.groovy:25:     * Returns contents of an index.json file from given directory.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/Utils.groovy:30:        return extractJsonFile(dir.resolve('index.json'))\n./stats/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-paranamer/2.19.0/execution-metrics.json:107:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-paranamer/2.19.0/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_module/jackson_module_paranamer/BytecodeReadingParanamerTest.java\",\n./stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-xpath/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json:58:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-xpath/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_xpath/FunctionTableTest.java\",\n./docs/support/index.html:561:        return `${rawBaseUrl}/metadata/${encodeURIComponent(group)}/${encodeURIComponent(artifact)}/index.json`;\n./stats/org.apache.yetus/audience-annotations/0.12.0/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.apache.yetus/audience-annotations/0.12.0/src/test/java/org_apache_yetus/audience_annotations/Audience_annotationsTest.java\",\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:44:- An artifact-level `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` that records, per metadata version: tested library versions, allowed packages, source/test/documentation URLs, optional `requires`, `default-for`, `skipped-versions`, and `override` flags.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:131:    Repo->>Artifact: package metadata/** + index.json files\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:136:    Artifact-->>NBT: metadata + index.json per artifact\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:137:    NBT->>NBT: for each application dependency,<br/>pick metadata version via index.json<br/>(tested-versions → default-for → latest)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:154:<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json                        # one per supported artifact (element 2)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:159:Plugin-relevant content is `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` and the per-version `reachability-metadata.json` files; the plugin discovers libraries by directory walk. `library-and-framework-list.json` and `schemas/` are present for downstream tooling (the libraries-and-frameworks page and offline validators) and are not consumed by native-build-tools at native-image time.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:167:**4. Version-selection algorithm.** Given an application dependency `g:a:v`, native-build-tools loads the `index.json` array of `g/a/` and applies a primary lookup, picking the first entry that matches in this order:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:176:    Start([\"Application dependency<br/>g:a:v\"]) --> LoadIndex[\"Load <code>g/a/index.json</code><br/>(array of entries)\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:205:- **FR-M-5** Each `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/` directory must include a valid `index.json` enumerating its metadata versions and tested library versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:206:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:212:- **FR-T-2** Tests live under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>` unless an `index.json` entry sets `test-version` to share a suite across versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:216:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:265:- An `index.json` describing metadata versions and tested versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:270:- Validated metadata + tests + index.json under `metadata/` and `tests/src/`.\n./docs/CI.md:27:  - Triggers: PRs to master touching [metadata/](../metadata/) or [tests/src/](../tests/src/).\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, includes newly added tested versions from artifact-level index diffs, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\n./docs/CI.md:46:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/), then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./stats/org.apache.yetus/audience-annotations/0.14.0/execution-metrics.json:83:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.apache.yetus/audience-annotations/0.14.0/src/test/java/org_apache_yetus/audience_annotations/Audience_annotationsTest.java\",\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/CheckMetadataFilesAllTask.java:38:            getLogger().lifecycle(\"No matching coordinates found for metadata checks. Nothing to do.\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:228:    tasks.register(\"tckClean\", CleanInvocationTask.class) { t ->\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:232:    tasks.named(\"clean\").configure { it.dependsOn(\"tckClean\") }\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:2